b'' b'archive-name: graphics/resources-list/part2' b'last-modified: b'' b'' b'computer graphics resource listing weekly posting part b'===================================================' b'last change april b'' b'' b'14. plotting packages' b'=====================' b'' b'gnuplot b'-----------' b'it is one of the best and 3-d plotting packages, with' b"online help.it's a command-line driven interactive function plotting utility" b'for unix, msdos, amiga, archimedes, and vms platforms (at least!).' b'freely distributed, it supports many terminals, plotters, and printers' b'and is easily extensible to include new devices.' b'it was posted to comp.sources.misc in version plus patches.' b'you can practically find it everywhere (use archie to find a site near you!).' b'the comp.graphics.gnuplot newsgroup is devoted to discussion of gnuplot.' b'' b'xvgr and xmgr (ace/gr)' b'-----------------------' b'xmgr is an xy-plotting tool for unix workstations using' b'x or openwindows. there is an xview version called xvgr for' b'suns. collectively, these tools are known as ace/gr.' b'compiling xmgr requires the motif toolkit version b'and x11r4 xmgr will not compile under x11r3/motif 1.0x.' b'' b'check at ftp.ccalmr.ogi.edu in' b'/ccalmr/pub/acegr/xmgr-2.09.tar.z (motif version)' b'/ccalmr/pub/acegr/xvgr-2.09.tar.z (xview version)' b'' b'comments, suggestions, bug reports to paul j turner' b'due to time constraints, replies will be few and far between.' b'' b'robot' b'-----' b'release 2-d and limited 3-d. based on xview written' b'in c fortran (so you need a fortran compiler or the f2c translator).' b'mainly tested on sun4, less on decstations. check at' b'ftp.astro.psu.edu pub/astrod.' b'' b'vg plotting library' b'-------------------' b'this is a library of fortran callable routines at sunspot.ceee.nist.gov' b'[129.6.64.151]' b'' b'xgobi' b'-----' b"it's being developed at bellcore, and its speciality are" b'multidimensional data sets analysis and exploration. you can call it' b'from the s language also, and it works as an x11 client using the athena' b"widget set (or with an ascii terminal). it's distributed free of charge" b'from statlib at cmu.' b'in the body area of the message, put the line' b'' b'send xgobi from general' b'' b'if you want to pick it via ftp, connect to lib.stat.cmu.edu. log in as' b'"statlib" and use your e-mail address as your password. then type' b'' b'cd general' b'mget xgobi.*' b'' b"warning: it's about mb sources large postscript manual. read the" b'relevant readme to decide whether you need it or not.' b'' b'pgplot' b'------' b"runs on vax/vms and supposedly on unix. it's a set of fortran routines freely" b'available (though copyrighted and requiring a nominal fee of or so)' b'that includes contour plots and support for various devices, including ps.' b'' b'ggraph' b'------' b'host shorty.cs.wisc.edu /pub/ggraph.tar.z' b'unknown more details.' b'' b'epigraph' b'--------' b'you can get the program demo or (and) play version, if sent to' b'' b'1251 budapest posta fiok b'hungary' b'ph/fax budapest' b'ph b'' b'multiplot xln' b'-------------' b'for amigas, shareware usd, uk or aust.). advanced 2d package' b'that has a big list of features. contact:' b'' b'cambridge university' b'department of pathology,' b'tennis court road,' b'cambridge cb2 1qp, uk' b'' b'' b'+athena plotter widget set' b'+-------------------------' b'+' b"+ this version v6.0 is based on gregory bond's version v5-beta. added" b'+ some stuff for scientific graphs, i.e. log axes, free scalable axes,' b'+ xy-lineplots and some more, and re-added plotter callbacks from v4, e.g.' b'+ to request the current pointer position, or to cut off a rectangle from the' b'+ plotting area for zooming-in. version v6.0 has a log of bugs fixed and a' b'+ log of improvements against v6-beta. additionally i did some other' b'+ changes/extensions, besides' b'+' b'+ origin and frame lines for axes.' b'+ subgrid lines on subtic positions.' b'+ line plots in different line types (lines, points, lines+points,' b'+ impulses, lines+impulses, steps, bars), line styles (solid, dotted,' b'+ dashed, dot-dashed) and marker types for data points.' b'+ legend at the right or left hand side of the plot.' b'+ optional drawing to a pixmap instead of a window.' b'+ layout callback for aligning axis positions when using' b'+ multiple plotters in one application.' b'+' b'+ available at export.lcs.mit.edu, directory contrib/plotter' b'+' b'+sciplot' b'+-------' b'+ sciplot is a scientific 2d plotting and manipulation program.' b"+ for the next (requires nextstep and it's shareware." b'+' b'+ features:' b'+ ascii import and export; eps export; copy, cut, paste with data buffer;' b'+ free number of data points, data buffer, and document window;' b'+ selective open and save plotting in many styles; automatic legend;' b'+ subviews; linear and logarithmic axes; two different axes; text and graphic;' b'+ color support; zoom; normalizing and moving; axis conversions;' b'+ free hand data manipulations (cut, edit, move, etc.); data editor; sorting' b'+ of data; absolute,relative, and free defined error bars;' b'+ calculating with buffers background subtractions' b'+ (linear,shirley,tougaard, bezier); integration and relative integration;' b'+ fitting of one or more free defined functions; linear regression;' b'+ calculations sin, cos, log, etc.); function generator;' b'+ spline interpolation; least square smooth and fft smooth; differentiation;' b'+ fft; esca calculations and database; and something more' b'+' b'+ you can find it on:' b'+ ftp.cs.tu-berlin.de /pub/next/science/sciplot3.1.tar.z' b'+' b'+ author:' b'+ michael wesemann' b'+ scillerstr. berlin germany' b'+' b'+plplot' b'+------' b'+ plplot is a scientific plotting package for many systems, small (micro)' b'+ and large (super) alike. despite its small size and quickness,' b'+ it has enough power to satisfy most users, including:' b'+ standard x-y plots, semilog plots, log-log plots, contour plots, 3d plots,' b'+ mesh plots, bar charts and pie charts. multiple graphs (of the same or' b'+ different sizes) may be placed on a single page with multiple lines in each' b'+ graph. different line styles, widths and colors are supported. a virtually' b'+ infinite number of distinct area fill patterns may be used. there are' b'+ almost characters in the extended character set. this includes four' b'+ different fonts, the greek alphabet and a host of mathematical, musical, and' b'+ other symbols. the fonts can be scaled to any size for various effects.' b'+ many different output device drivers are available (system dependent),' b'+ including a portable metafile format and renderer.' b'+' b'+ freely available (but copyrighted) via anonymous ftp on' b'+ hagar.ph.utexas.edu, directory pub/plplot' b'+' b'+ at present (v. plplot is known to work on the following systems:' b'+' b'+ unix: sunos, a/ix, hp-ux, unicos, dg/ux, ultrix' b'+ other platforms: vms, amiga/exec, ms-dos, os/2, next' b'+' b'+ authors: many. the main supporters are:' b'+' b'+ xterm, xwindow, tektronix, and amiga drivers.' b'+' b'+supermongo' b'+----------' b'+ 2-d plotting package at cmu, filename ~re00/tmp/sm.2.1.0.tar.z' b'+ (probably under the ftp.cmu.edu or andrew.cmu.edu machines?)' b'+' b'+gle' b'+---' b'+ gle is a high quality graphics package for scientists. it runs on a' b'+ variety of platforms (pcs, vaxes, and unix) with drivers for xwindows,' b'+ regis, tek4010, pc graphics cards, vt100s, hp plotters, postscript' b'+ printers, epson-compatible printers and laserjet/paintjet printers. it' b'+ provides latex quality fonts, as well as full support for postscript' b'+ fonts. the graphing module provides full control over all features of' b'+ graphs. the graphics primitives include user-defined subroutines for' b'+ complex pictures and diagrams.' b'+' b'+ accompanying utilities include surface (for hidden line surface' b'+ plotting), contour (for contour plots), manip (for manipulation of' b'+ columnar data files), and fitls (for fitting arbitrary equations to' b'+ data).' b'+' b'+ mailing list: glelist. send a message to' b'+' b'+' b'+ sub glelist "your name"' b'+' b'' b'==========================================================================' b'' b'15. image analysis software image processing and display' b'==========================================================' b'' b'pc and mac-based tools (multi-platform software)' b'======================' b'' b'imdisp' b'------' b'imdisp written at jpl and other nasa sites. can do simple display,' b'enhancing, smoothing and so on. works with the fits and vicar/pds' b'data formats of nasa. can read tiff images, if you know their dimensions' b'[pc and macs]' b'' b'labview b'---------' b'labview is used as a framework for image processing tools. it provides a' b'graphical programming environment using block diagram sketch is the' b'"program" with graphical elements representing the programming elements.' b'hundreds of functions are already available and are connected using a' b'wiring tool to create the block diagram (program). functions that the' b'block diagrams represent include digital signal processing and' b'filtering, numerical analysis, statistics, etc. the tool allows any' b'virtual instrument (vi, a software file that looks and acts like a real' b'laboratory instrument) to be used as a part of any other virtual' b'instrument.' b'' b'national instruments markets plug-in digital signal processing (dsp)' b'boards for macintoshs and pc compatables that allow real-time' b'acquisition and analysis at a personal computer. new software tools for' b'dsp are allowing engineers to harness the power of this technology. the' b'tools range from low-level debugging software to high-level block' b'diagram development software. there are three levels of dsp programming' b'associated with the nb-dsp2300 board and labview:' b'use of the nb-dsp2300 analysis library: ffts, power spectra, filters' b'routines callable from think c and macintosh programers workshop (mpw) c' b'that execute on the nb-dsp2300 board. there is an analysis virtual' b'interface library of ready-to-use vis optimized for the nb-dsp2300.' b'' b'use of the national instruments developers toolkit that includes an' b'optimizing c compiler, an assembler and a linker for low-level' b'programming of the dsp hardware. this approach offers the highest level' b'of performance but is the must difficult in terms of ease of use.' b'' b'use of the national instruments interface kit software package which has' b'utility functions for memory management data communications and' b'downloading code to the nb-dsp2300 board. (this is the easiest route for' b'the development of custom code.)' b'' b'ultimage concept vi' b'-------------------' b'concept vi by graftek-france is a family of image processing virtual' b'instruments (vis) that give labview (described above) users high-end' b'tools for designing, integrating and monitoring imaging control systems.' b'a vi is a software file that looks and acts like a real laboratory' b'instrument. typical applications for concept vi include thermography,' b'surveillance, machine vision, production testing, biomedical imaging,' b'electronic microscopy and remote sensing.' b'' b'ultimage concept vi addresses applications which require further' b'qualitative and quantitative analysis. it includes a complete set of' b'functions for image enhancement, histogram equalization, spatial and' b'frequency filtering, isolation of features, thresholding, mathematical' b'morphology analysis, density measurement, object counting, sizing and' b'characterization.' b'' b'the program loads images with a minimum resolution of by a pixel' b'depth of or bits, and one image plane. standard input and' b'output formats include pict, tiff, satie, and aipd. other formats can' b'be imported.' b'' b'image enhancement features include lookup table transformations, spatial' b'linear and non-linear filters, frequency filtering, arithmetic and logic' b'operations, and geometric transformations, among others. morphological' b'transformations include erosion, dilation, opening, closing, hole' b'removal, object separation, and extraction of skeletons, among others.' b"quantitative analysis provides for objects' detection, measurement, and" b'morphological distribution. measures include area, perimeter, center of' b'gravity, moment of inertia, orientation, length of relevant chords, and' b'shape factors and equivalence. measures are saved in ascii format. the' b'program also provides for macro scripting and integration of custom' b'modules.' b'' b'a 3-d view command plots a perspective data graph where image intensity' b'is depicted as mountains or valleys in the plot. the histogram tool can' b'be plotted with either a linear or logarithmic scale. the twenty-eight' b'arithmetic and logical operations provide for: masking and averaging' b'sections of images, noise removal, making comparisons, etc. there are' b'13 spatial filters that alter pixel intensities based on local' b'intensity. these include high-pass filters for contrast and outlines.' b'the frequency data resulting from fft analysis can be displayed as' b'either the (real imaginary components or the (phase, magnitude)' b'data. the morphological transformations are useful for data sharpening' b'and defining objects or for removing artifacts.' b'' b'the transformations include: thresholding, eroding, dilating and even' b'hole filling.' b'' b"the program's quantitative analysis measurements include: area," b'perimeter, center of mass, object counts, and angle between points.' b'' b'gtfs, inc. bennett valley road #100c santa rosa, ca b'707-579-1733' b'' b'iplab spectrum' b'--------------' b'iplab spectrum supports image processing and analysis but lacks the' b'morphology and quantitative analysis features provided by' b'graftek-franceus ultimage concept vi. using scripting tools, the user' b'tells the system the operations to be performed. the problem is that far' b'too many basic operations require manual intervention. the tool' b'supports: ffts, arithmetic operations for pixel alteration, and a' b'movie command for cycling through windows.' b'' b'' b'macintosh-based tools' b'=====================' b'' b'ncsa image, ncsa paledit and more' b'---------------------------------' b'ncsa provides a whole suite of public-domain visualization tools for the' b'macintosh, primarily aimed at researchers wanting to visualize results' b'from numerical modelling calculations. these applications,' b'documentation, and source code are available for anonymous ftp from' b'ftp.ncsa.uiuc.edu. commercial versions of the ncsa programs have been' b'developed by spyglass.' b'' b'spyglass, inc. devonshire drive champaign, il b'fax: b'' b'nih image' b'---------' b'available at alw.nih.gov or (preferably)' b'zippy.nimh.nih.gov directory:/pub/image.' b'it has painting and image manipulation tools, a macro language,' b'tools for measuring areas, distances and angles, and for counting' b'things. using a frame grabber card, it can record sequences of' b'images to be played back as a movie. it can invoke user-defined' b'convolution matrix filters, such as gaussian. it can import raw' b'data in tab-delimited ascii, or as or 2-byte quantities. it also' b'does histograms and even 3-d plots. it is limited to 8-bits/pixel,' b'though the bits map into a color lookup table. it runs on any mac' b'that has a 256-color screen and a fpu (or get the nonfpu version' b'from zippy.nimh.nih.gov)' b'' b'photomac' b'--------' b'data translation, inc. locke dr. marlboro, ma b'' b'photopress' b'----------' b'blue solutions marigold place thousand oaks, ca b'' b'pixeltools and tcl-image' b'------------------------' b'"complete family of pixeltools (hardware accelerator and applications' b'software) for scientific image processing and analysis. video-rate' b'capture, display, processing, and analysis of high-resolution' b'monochromatic and color images. includes c source code."' b'' b'tcl-image:' b'"software package for scientific, quantitative image processing and' b'analysis. it provides a complete language for the capture, enhancement,' b'and extraction of quantitative information from gray-scale images.' b'tcl_image has over functions for image processing, and contains the' b'other elements needed in a full programming language for algorithm' b'development variables and control structures. it is easily' b'extensible through "script" (or indirect command) files. these script' b'files are simply text files that contain tcl-image commands. they are' b'executed as normal commands and include the ability to pass parameters.' b'the direct capture of video images is supported via popular frame' b'grabber boards. tcl-image comes with the i-view utility that provides' b'conversion between common image file types, such as pict2 and tiff."' b'' b'perceptics pellissippi parkway knoxville, tn b'' b'satellite image workshop' b'------------------------' b'it comes with a number of satellite pictures (raw data) and does all' b"sorts of image enhancing on it. you'll need at least a mac ii with co-" b"processor; a color display and a large harddisk. the program doesn't" b'run under system 7.x.ate1 v1' b'' b'in the documentation the contact address is given as: liz smith, jet' b'propulsion laboratory, ms oak grove dr,.pasadena, ca b'(818) b'' b'visualization workbench' b'-----------------------' b'"an electronic imaging software system that performs interactive image' b'analysis and scientific 2d and 3d plotting."' b'' b'paragon imagine lincoln st. lowell, ma b'' b'adobe photoshop' b'---------------' b'' b'the tool supports rtrue colors with 24-bit images or levels of grey' b'scale. once an image has been imported it can be rre-toucheds with' b'various editing tools typical of those used in macintosh-based rpaints' b'applications. these include an eraser, pencil, brush and air brush.' b'advanced rpastes tools that control the interaction between a pasted' b'selection and the receiving site have also been incorporated. for' b'example, all red pixels in a selection can easily be preventing from' b'being pasted. photoshop has transparencies ranging from to b'allowing you to create ghost overlays. rphoto-editings tools include' b'control of the brightness and contrast, color balancing, hue/saturation' b'modification and spectrum equalization. images can be subjected to' b'various signal processing algorithms to smooth or sharpen the image,' b'blur edges, or locate edges. image scaling is also supported.' b'' b'for storage savings, the images can be compressed using standard' b'algorithms, including externally supplied compression such as jpeg,' b'availlable from storm technologies. the latest version of adobe' b'photoshop supports the import of numerous image formats including: epsf,' b'epsf, tiff, pict resource, amiga iff/ilbm, compuserve gif, macpaint,' b'pixar, pixelpaint, scitex ct, tga and thunderscan..' b'' b'adobe systems, inc. charlestown road po box mountain view, ca' b'94039-7900 b'' b'colorstudio and imagestudio' b'---------------------------' b'colorstudio is an image-editing and paint package from letraset that has' b'more features than adobe photoshop but is decidedly more complex and' b'therefore more difficult to use. several steps are often required to' b'accomplish that which can be done in a single step using photoshop. the' b'application requires a great deal of available disk space as one can' b'easily end up with images in the mb range. the program provides a' b'variety of powerful selection tools including the "auto selection tool"' b'which lets the user choose image areas on the basis of color, close' b'hues, color range and mask.' b'' b"imagestudio: don't know..." b'' b'letraset usa eisenhower drive paramus, nj b'' b'dapple systems' b'--------------' b'"high resolution image analysis software provides processing tools to' b'work with multiple images, enhance and edit, and measure a variety of' b'global or feature parameters, and interpret the data."' b'' b'dapple systems, w. olive ave, sunnyvale, ca b'' b'digital darkroom' b'----------------' b'the latest release of digital darkroom has five new selection and' b'editing tools for enhancing images. one such feature allows the user to' b'select part of an image simply by "painting" it. a new polyline' b'selection tool creates a selection tool for single pixel wide' b'selections. a brush lets the operator "paint" with a selected portion' b'of the image. note that this is not a true color image enhancement tool.' b'this tool should be used when the user intends to operate in grey-scale' b'images only. it should be noted that digital darkroom is not as' b'powerful as either adobe photoshop or colorstudio.' b'' b'silicon beach software carroll ctr. rd., suite j san diego, ca' b'92126 b'' b'dimple' b'------' b'it is compatible with system and system requires mac lc or' b'ii series with colours, with a recommended min of 6mb of ram. it has' b'the capability of reading erdas files. functions include; image' b'enhancement, 3d and contour plots, image statistics, supervised and' b'unsupervised classification, pca and other image transformations. there' b'is also a means (image operation language or iol) by which you can write' b'your own transformations. there is no image rectification, however' b'dimple is compatable with mapii. the latest version is and it is in' b'the beta stage of testing. dimple was initially developed as a teaching' b'tool and it is very good for this purpose."' b'' b'"dimple runs on a colour macintosh. it is a product still in its' b"development phase.. i.e. it doesn't have all the inbuilt features of" b'other packages, but is coming along nicely. it has its own inbuilt' b'language for writing "programs" for processing an image, defining' b'convolution filters etc. dimple is a full mac application with pull down' b'menus etc... it is unprotected software."' b'' b'process software solutions, po box wollongong, new south wales,' b'australia. phone fax b'' b'enhance' b'-------' b'enhance has a rrulers tool that supports measurements and additionally' b'provides angle data. the tool has over mathematical filter' b'variations: "laplacian, medium noise filter", etc. files can be saved' b"as either tiff, pict, epsf or text (however epsf files can't be imported)." b'' b'microfrontier hickman road des moines, ia b'' b'image analyst' b'-------------' b'an image processing product for users who need to extract quantitative' b'data from video images. image analyst lets users configure' b'sophisticated image processing and measurement routines without the' b'necessity of knowing a programming language. it is designed for such' b'tasks at computing number and size of cells in images projected by video' b'cameras attached to microscopes, or enhancing and measuring distances in' b'radiographs.' b'' b'image analyst provides users with an array of field-proven video' b'analysis techniques that enable them to easily assemble a sequence of' b'instructions to enhance feature appearance; count objects; determine' b'density, shape, size, position, or movement; perform object feature' b'extraction; and conduct textural analysis automatically. image analyst' b'works with either a framegrabber board and any standard video camera, or' b'a disk-stored image.' b'' b'within minutes, without the need for programming, the image analyst user' b'can set up a process to identify and analyze any element of a image.' b'measurements and statistics can be automatically or semi-automatically' b'generated from tiff or pict files or from captured video tape images.' b'image analyst recognizes items in images based on their size, shape and' b'position. the tool provides direct support for the data translation and' b'scion frame grabbers. a menu command allows for image capture from a vcr' b'video camera or other ntsc or pal devices.' b'' b'there are types of files, the image itself and the related sequence' b'file that holds the processing, measurements and analysis that the user' b'defines. automated sequences are set up in regions of interest (roi)' b'represented by movable, sizable boxes atop the image. inside a roi, the' b'program can find the distance between two edges, the area of a shape,' b'the thickness of a wall, etc. image analyst finds the center, edge and' b'other positions automatically. the application also provides tools so' b'that the user can work interactively to find the edge of object. it also' b'supports histograms and a color look-up table (clut) tool.' b'' b'automatix, inc. middlesex turnpike billerica, ma b'' b'iplab' b'-----' b'signal analytics corp. maple ave. e vienna, va b'fax b'' b'"menu-driven image processing software that supports 24-bit color or' b'pseudocolor/grayscale image display and manipulation."' b'' b'map ii' b'------' b'among the mac gis systems, map ii distributed by john wiley has' b'integrated image analysis.' b'' b'image' b'-----' b'from stanford try anonymous ftp from sumex-aim.stanford.edu' b'it has pd source for image v2, and ready to run code for a mac under' b'image v3.' b'' b'' b'' b'windows/dos pc-based tools' b'==========================' b'' b'ccd' b'---' b"richard berry's ccd imaging book for willamon-bell contains (optional?)" b'disks with image manipulating software. source code is included.' b'' b'erdas' b'-----' b'"erdas will do all of the things you want: rectification,' b'classification, transformations (canned user-defined), overlays,' b'filters, contrast enhancement, etc. i was using it on my thesis b'then changed the topic a bit that work became secondary."' b'' b'erdas, inc. buford highway suite atlanta, ga b'fax b'' b'rsvga' b'-----' b'"i have been getting up to speed on a program called rsvga available from' b"eidetic digital image ltd. in british columbia. its for ibm pc's or" b'clones, cheap (about and does all the stuff erdas does but is not' b'as fast or as power