ssing) is a powerful' b'system providing both user friendliness and high functionality in' b'interactive times.' b'' b'feature description' b'' b'disimp incorporates a rich library of image processing utilities and' b'spatial data options. all functions can be easily accessed via the' b'disimp executive. this menu is modular in design and groups image' b'processes by their function. such a logical structure means that' b'complicated processes are simply a progression through a series of' b'modules.' b'' b'processes include image rectification, classification (unsupervised and' b'supervised), intensity transformations, three dimensional display and' b'principal component analysis. disimp also supports the more simple and' b'effective enhancement techniques of filtering, band subtraction and' b'ratioing.' b'' b'host configuration requirements' b'' b'running on unix workstations, disimp is capable of processing the more' b'computational intensive techniques in interactive processing times.' b"disimp is available in both runtime and programmer's environments. using" b'the programmers environment, utilities can be developed for specific' b'applications programs.' b'' b'graphics are governed by an icon-based display panel which allows quick' b'enhancments of a displayed image. manipulations of look up tables,' b'colour stretches, changes to histograms, zooming and panning can be' b'interactively driven through this control.' b'' b'a range of geographic projections enables disimp to integrate data of' b'image, graphic and textual types. images can be rectified by a number of' b'coordinate systems, providing the true geographic knowledge essential' b'for ground truthing. overlays of grids, text and vector data can be' b'added to further enhance referenced imagery.' b'' b'the system is a flexible package allowing users of various skill levels' b'to determine their own working environment, including the amount of help' b'required. disimp comes fully configured with no optiona