dge detection and line drawing manipulation, digital' b'image compression and transmission methods, noise generation, and image' b'statistics computation. over such image transformation programs' b'have been developed. as a result, almost any image processing task' b'can be performed quickly and conveniently. additionally, hips allows' b'users to easily integrate their own custom routines. new users' b'become effective using hips on their first day.' b'' b'hips features images that are self-documenting. each image stored in' b'the system contains a history of the transformations that have been' b'applied to that image. hips includes a small set of subroutines' b'which primarily deals with a standardized image sequence header, and' b'a large library of image transformation tools in the form of unix' b"``filters''. it comes complete with source code, on-line manual" b'pages, and on-line documentation.' b'' b'host configuration requirements' b'' b'originally developed at new york university, hips now represents' b'one of the most extensive and flexible vision and image processing' b'environments currently available. it runs under the unix operating' b'system. it is modular and flexible, provides automatic documentation' b'of its actions, and is almost entirely independent of special equipment.' b'hips is now in use on a variety of computers including vax and' b'microvax, sun, apollo, masscomp, ncr tower, iris, ibm at, etc.' b'for image display and input, drivers are supplied for the grinnell and' b'adage (ikonas) image processors, and the sun-2, sun-3, sun- and' b'sun-386i consoles. we also supply user-contributed drivers for a' b'number of other framestores and windowing packages (sun gfx, sun' b'console, matrox vip-1024, iti ip-512, lexidata, macintosh ii, x' b'windowing system, and iris). the hipsaddon package includes an' b'interface for the crs-4000. it is a simple matter to interface hips' b'with other frame- stores, and we can put interested users in touch with' b'users who have interfaced hips with the arlunya and datacube max-' b'video. hips can be easily adapted for other image display devices' b'because of hips is machine independent.' b'' b'availability' b'' b'hips has proven itself a highly flexible system, both as an' b'interactive research tool, and for more production- oriented tasks. it' b'is both easy to use, and quickly adapted and extended to new uses. hips' b'is supplied on magnetic tape in unix tar format (either reel- to-reel or' b'sun cartridge), and comes with source code, libraries, a library of' b'convolu- tion masks, and on-line documentation and manual pages.' b'' b'michael landy sharpimage software p.o. box prince street station' b'new york, ny voice: fax: b'' b'' b'mira' b'----' b"[ please don't confuse that with the thalmanns animation system from" b'montreal. these are altogether different beasts! nfotis b'' b'mira stands for microcomputer image reduction and analysis. mira gives' b'workstation level performance on dos computers using svga cards in' b'256 color modes up to 1024x768. mira contains a very handsome/functional' b'gui which is mouse and keystroke operated. mira reads/writes tiff and fits' b'formats, native formats of a number of ccd cameras, and uncompressed binary' b'images in byte, short integer, and 4-byte real pixel format in or b'dimensions. the result of an image processing operation can be short integer' b'or real pixels, or the same as that of the input image. mira does the' b'operation using short or floating point arithmetic to maintain the precision' b'and accuracy of the pixel format. over functions are hand-coded in' b'assembly language for maximum speed on the intel hardware. the entire' b'graphical interface is also written in assembly language to maximize' b'the speed of windowing operations. windows for 2-d image and 1-d image/data' b'display and analysis have dedicated cursors which read position and value' b'value in real time as you move the mouse. there are also smooth, real time' b'contrast and brightness stretch and panning of a magnified portion of' b'the displayed image(s), all operated by the mouse. a wide selection of' b'grayscale, pseudocolor, and random palettes is provided, and other' b'palettes can be generated.' b'' b'' b'supported functions include such niceties as the following:' b'' b'o image image: interpolation' b'o image constant: b'o unary operations: abs value, polynomial of pixel value, chs, 1/x, log,' b'byteswap, clip values at upper/lower limits, short-real or real-short.' b'o combine images by mean, median, mode, or sum of pixel values, with or' b'without autoscaling to mean, median, or mode of an image section.' b'o convolutions/filters: laplacian, sobel edge operator, directional gradient,' b'line, gaussian, elliptical and rectangular equal weight filters, unsharp' b'masking, median filters, user defined filter kernel. ellipse, rectangle,' b'line, gradient, gaussian, and user defined filters can be rotated to' b'any specified angle.' b'o ccd data reduction: flat fielding, dark subtraction, column over/underscan' b'bias removal, remove bad pixels and column defects, normalize to' b'region target mean, median, or modal value.' b'o create subimage, mosaic m x n 1-d or 2-d images to get larger image,' b'collapse 2-d image into 1-d image.' b'o plot 1-d section or collapsed section of 2-d image, plot histogram of' b'region of an image.' b'o review/change image information/header data, rename keywords, plot' b'keyword values for a set of images.' b'o luminance/photometry: elliptical or circular aperture photometry,' b'brightness profile, isophotal photometry between set of upper lower' b'luminances, area and luminance inside traced polygon. interactive' b'background fitting and removal from part or all of image, fit elliptical' b'aperture shape to image isophotes.' b'o interactive with 2-d image: contrast/brightness, x- y- or diagonal plot' b'of pixel values, distance between two points, compute region stats